# Real-Time Geometric Shape Detection, Automated Quality Inspection and Production Monitoring System Using OpenCV

## Overview

This project was developed to demonstrate how computer vision can be applied to automate quality inspection in a manufacturing environment. The system uses Python and OpenCV to detect geometric shapes in real time, identify their colors, compare manufactured components with a reference image, and determine whether they satisfy predefined quality standards.

In addition to shape detection, the project includes object tracking, defect detection, production monitoring, CSV report generation, and automatic storage of defective part images. The objective was to build a practical prototype that reflects the basic workflow followed in industrial visual inspection systems.

## Features

- Real-time detection of multiple geometric shapes
- Color identification using the HSV color space
- Human detection using OpenCV's Haar Cascade classifier
- Object tracking with unique IDs
- Automated quality inspection using a reference image
- Detection of manufacturing defects
- PASS/FAIL classification
- Live production dashboard
- Automatic CSV report generation
- Automatic saving of defective product images
- Contour difference visualization for defect analysis

