## How It Works

The application captures live video from a webcam and processes each frame using a sequence of computer vision techniques.

The processing pipeline consists of:

1. Capture the live image.
2. Convert the image to grayscale.
3. Apply Gaussian Blur to reduce noise.
4. Detect object edges using the Canny Edge Detector.
5. Find contours of detected objects.
6. Identify the geometric shape and object color.
7. Track detected objects.
8. Compare manufactured parts with a reference object.
9. Detect any defects or dimensional differences.
10. Classify the part as PASS or FAIL.
11. Update the production dashboard and generate inspection reports.

## Quality Inspection

The quality inspection module compares every manufactured component with a previously selected reference component.

The comparison includes:

- Shape verification
- Size comparison
- Number of vertices
- Number of holes
- Solidity comparison
- Contour similarity

If the inspected component satisfies all predefined conditions, it is marked as PASS. Otherwise, it is marked as FAIL, and the detected defect is recorded.

## Defects Detected

The system is capable of identifying several common manufacturing defects, including:

- Shape mismatch
- Missing corners
- Broken edges
- Extra material
- Missing material
- Additional holes
- Missing holes
- Incorrect dimensions
- Deformed components

## Production Dashboard

During inspection, the system continuously displays:

- Total inspected components
- Number of accepted components
- Number of rejected components
- Production efficiency

This provides a quick overview of the inspection process in real time.

## Report Generation

For every inspected component, the system automatically creates a CSV report containing:

- Date and time
- Shape
- Color
- Inspection result
- Defect description
- Image location

Whenever a defective component is detected, the corresponding inspection image and contour comparison image are also saved automatically.

